AI systems often collect and analyze personal data—like browsing habits, location, and biometrics—without clear consent. These systems infer sensitive details, such as political views or mental health, and may share data with third parties. Worse, many users can’t access or delete their data, even when requested. This lack of control turns individuals into passive data sources, undermining autonomy and privacy rights. Companies profit from personal data while offering minimal transparency, creating a power imbalance where users have little say over how their information is used. We need stronger regulations to protect digital rights and ensure AI respects human dignity.